I clone this directory into my home folder, then link each file to where it belongs:

ln -s:
christhekeele.zsh-theme => ~/.oh-my-zsh/themes/christhekeele.zsh-theme OR ~/.zsh-themes/christhekeele.zsh-theme
.zshrc => ~/.zshrc
zshenv => /etc/zshenv (requires sudo)

NOTE: Use absolute paths when running ln -s or you'll die.

